Interface Renderer

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    FakeRenderer, Renderer_Impl

    public interface Renderer
    An interface for rendering the content of the game.

    • Method Detail

      • setMaze

        boolean setMaze(MazeState maze)
        Sets the board layout to be rendered. A null state disables all rendering.
        Parameters:
        maze - the MazeState comprising the board
        Returns:
        a boolean representing whether the map was successfully rendered

      • getMaze

        MazeState getMaze()
        Retrieves the current board layout that is being rendered.
        Returns:
        a MazeState comprising the currently rendered board.

      • setFocusArea

        boolean setFocusArea(java.awt.Rectangle area)
        Changes the focus area (displayed region) of the board. Until resetFocusArea() is called, this also disables automatic adjustment of it. The Rectangle comprising the new area must have a width and height of 9.
        Parameters:
        area - the new focus region
        Returns:
        a boolean representing whether the focus region was changed

      • resetFocusArea

        void resetFocusArea()
        Resets the focus area to its default value, enabling automatic adjustment of it.

      • getFocusArea

        java.awt.Rectangle getFocusArea()
        Retrieves the current focus area (displayed region) of the board. Should setFocusArea() not be called, this is computed by the last call of redraw().
        Returns:
        the current focus area as a Rectangle.

      • getMaxPoint

        java.awt.Point getMaxPoint()
        Gets the maximum coordinates of the map to draw, using the current focus area.
        Returns:
        a Point with the x and y coordinates

      • getMinPoint

        java.awt.Point getMinPoint()
        Gets the minimum coordinates of the map to draw, using the current focus area.
        Returns:
        a Point with the x and y coordinates

      • getCellSize

        int getCellSize()
        Retrieves the cell size as rendered by the last call of redraw(). If redraw() has not been called, -1 is returned.
        Returns:
        the size of tiles drawn as an int.

      • getRenderedItems

        java.util.HashSet<java.lang.Object> getRenderedItems()
        Returns a HashSet of item and actor Objects rendered by the last call of redraw(). If redraw() has not been called, -1 is returned.
        Returns:
        all rendered items and actors as an HashMap of Objects.

      • getRenderedTiles

        java.util.HashSet<java.awt.Point> getRenderedTiles()
        Returns a HashSet of Pointss representing the locations of tiles rendered by the last call of redraw(). If redraw() has not been called, -1 is returned.
        Returns:
        all rendered tiles as an HashMap of Objects.

      • setNotice

        void setNotice(Notice notice)
        Displays a Notice on the board. If notice is null, displays nothing.
        Parameters:
        notice - the Notice to display.

      • getNotice

        Notice getNotice()
        Retrieves the current Notice that is displayed by the board.
        Returns:
        the current Notice.

      • hideNotice

        boolean hideNotice()
        Hides any displayed Notices.
        Returns:
        a boolean indicating whether a Notice was formerly displayed or not

      • redraw

        void redraw(java.awt.Graphics g,
            java.awt.Dimension size)
        Redraws the game panel in accord with the specified layout.
        Parameters:
        g - the Graphics item to use
        size - the size of the canvas to draw upon
